title: Storm Re-Sign Defensive Back Jon Setzer
text:
Storm Re-Sign Defensive Back Jon Setzer October 8, 2015, 8:01 AM 
Sioux Falls, SD - The Storm is pleased to announce the re-signing of defensive weapon, Jonathon Setzer. Jon will be entering his third season with the Storm. Setzer (5'10' 180lb, Winston Salem State University) proved to be a constant weapon last season as he accumulated 45 tackles, 35 solo, one interception, one safety, and two pass breakups. He will be an outstanding returning role model for the rookies on the team this year. General Manager Tyler Pederson stated, "Happy to have Jon back with us, his character and leadership is hard to replace. I know he is determined to make 2016 his best season yet." At the end of last season, Jon signed a one-year deal with the Arena Football Leagueâ€™s (AFL) Spokane Shock.
